    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your tomato plants are having a bit of a \"goblin\" problem. You might be dealing with a case of \"leaf yellowing,\" which can be caused by a few different things. First, let's check if your plants are getting enough sunlight. Just like goblins need a good spot to hide, your plants need plenty of light to thrive. If they're not getting enough, they might start to look a bit pale and yellow.\n\nNext, let's consider the soil. Goblins love to dig around, so your plants might be feeling the same way. Make sure your soil is well-draining and rich in nutrients. If it's too compacted or lacking in nutrients, your plants might start to show signs of distress, like yellowing leaves.\n\nLastly, check for pests. Goblins are notorious for their sneaky ways, and so are some pests that can harm your plants. Look for any signs of insects or disease, and take action if you find any.\n\nRemember, just like goblins, plants need the right conditions to thrive. Keep an eye on them and they'll be happy to grow strong and healthy. Good luck!",
